<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Error - Honeypot</title>
  <style>
    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

    body {
      font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Monaco', 'Courier New', monospace;
      background: #0d1117;
      color: #c9d1d9;
      padding: 20px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 100vh;
    }

    .error-container {
      max-width: 600px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 48px;
      color: #f85149;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    p {
      font-size: 18px;
      color: #8b949e;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
    }

    .error-details {
      background: #161b22;
      padding: 20px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid #da3633;
      border-left: 4px solid #da3633;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
      text-align: left;
    }

    .error-details code {
      color: #f85149;
      font-family: monospace;
    }

    .button {
      background: #238636;
      color: white;
      padding: 12px 24px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 600;
      display: inline-block;
      transition: all 0.2s;
    }

    .button:hover {
      background: #2ea043;
      transform: translateY(-1px);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="error-container">
    <h1>‚ö†Ô∏è Connection Error</h1>
    <p>Unable to connect to the honeypot process</p>

    <div class="error-details">
      <code><%= error_message %></code>
    </div>

    <p style="font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
      Make sure the honeypot is running: <code style="color: #58a6ff;">ruby honeypot.rb</code>
    </p>

    <a href="/dashboard" class="button">üîÉ Try Again</a>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
